HEADWORD: Hereafter
<hw>Here*aft"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>h⟦emac⟧r⟦ae⟧fter</ets>.]</ety> <def>In time to come; in some future
time or state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Hereafter</qex> he from war shall come.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hereafter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hereafter
<hw>Here*aft"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A future existence or
state.</def> <-- Syn. afterlife, the life to come, future life, eternal
bliss, eternal reward, -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'Tis Heaven itself that points out an <qex>hereafter</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hereafterward</ent>⟦br⟧
